}We can monitor the job status using  with the  returned on job creation. The following are valid statuses during the lifecycle of a job: – The job is marked  when the JSON file is ready to be processed by Amazon Bedrock for inference. – The job is marked  when Amazon Bedrock starts processing the JSON file. – The job is marked  if there was an error while processing. The error can be written into the JSON file as a part of . If it was a 4xx error, it’s written in the metadata of the Job. – The job is marked when the output JSON file is generated for the input JSON file and has been uploaded to the S3 output path submitted as a part of the  in . – The job is marked  when a  API is called on a job that is . A terminal state job ( or ) can’t be stopped using .The following is example code for the  API:GET /model-invocation-job/jobIdentifier HTTP/1.1

Response:
